Class SchemaManager

java.lang.Object
  org.dmd.dms.SchemaManager
All Implemented Interfaces:
DmcNameResolverIF
public class SchemaManager
extends java.lang.Object
implements DmcNameResolverIF

The SchemaManager class manages the elements that comprise schemas: types, attributes, classes and schemas themselves.

schemaPreAdd

public void schemaPreAdd(DmcUncheckedObject sd)
                  throws ResultException,
                         DmcValueException
This method is called from the DmsSchemaParser to alert us that a new schema is about to be read. We check the schema for any schemaExtension attributes and, if we find any, attempt to instantiate the extension class (if we don't already have it). As well, we ensure that the schemas required for the schema extension are loaded.

Parameters:
sd - The schema about to be loaded.
Throws:
ResultException
DmcValueException

findNamedObject

public DmcNamedObjectIF findNamedObject(DmcObjectName name,
                                        int attributeID)
Description copied from interface: DmcNameResolverIF
Finds a named object based on its name and indicates the attribute via which the reference is being made. This method is used via the DmcObject and is primarily intended to handle the situation where we must resolve internal type definitions as opposed to class definitions. This is due to the fact that we create internal type definitions for classes that have the same name as the associated classes.

Specified by:
findNamedObject in interface DmcNameResolverIF
